  "book_pages": [
    {
      "_id": "page_math_1",
      "book_id": "book_math_101",
      "page_number": 1,
      "title": "1.1 Linear Equations",
      "title_ar": "1.1 المعادلات الخطية",
      "titleEn": "1.1 Linear Equations",
      "titleAr": "1.1 المعادلات الخطية",
      "content": "# 1.1 Linear Equations\n\nLinear equations are mathematical statements showing equality of two expressions of first-degree. For example:\n\n`y = mx + c`\n\nWhere `m` is the slope and `c` is the y-intercept. Try plotting a graph of `y = 2x + 1` to understand how it behaves.",
      "contentEn": "# 1.1 Linear Equations\n\nLinear equations are mathematical statements showing equality of two expressions of first-degree. For example:\n\n`y = mx + c`\n\nWhere `m` is the slope and `c` is the y-intercept. Try plotting a graph of `y = 2x + 1` to understand how it behaves.",
      "contentAr": "# 1.1 المعادلات الخطية\n\nالمعادلات الخطية هي عبارات رياضية توضح تساوي تعبيرين من الدرجة الأولى. على سبيل المثال:\n\n`y = mx + c`\n\nحيث `m` يمثل الميل و `c` يمثل نقطة التقاطع مع محور الصادات. جرب رسم المخطط البياني للمعادلة `y = 2x + 1` لفهم سلوكها."
    },
    {
      "_id": "page_math_2",
      "book_id": "book_math_101",
      "page_number": 2,
      "title": "1.2 Quadratic Basics",
      "title_ar": "1.2 أساسيات المعادلات التربيعية",
      "titleEn": "1.2 Quadratic Basics",
      "titleAr": "1.2 أساسيات المعادلات التربيعية",
      "content": "# 1.2 Quadratic Basics\n\nQuadratic equations are of the form:\n\n`ax^2 + bx + c = 0`\n\nWhere `a` is not zero. They can be solved using the quadratic formula:\n\n`x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / (2a)`\n\nLet's test this formula on `x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0` which yields `x = 2` and `x = 3`.",
      "contentEn": "# 1.2 Quadratic Basics\n\nQuadratic equations are of the form:\n\n`ax^2 + bx + c = 0`\n\nWhere `a` is not zero. They can be solved using the quadratic formula:\n\n`x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / (2a)`\n\nLet's test this formula on `x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0` which yields `x = 2` and `x = 3`.",
      "contentAr": "# 1.2 أساسيات المعادلات التربيعية\n\nتأخذ المعادلات التربيعية الشكل التالي:\n\n`ax^2 + bx + c = 0`\n\nحيث `a` لا يساوي الصفر. يمكن حلها باستخدام القانون العام للحل:\n\n`x = (-b ± sqrt(b^2 - 4ac)) / (2a)`\n\nلنختبر هذه الصيغة على المعادلة `x^2 - 5x + 6 = 0` والتي ينتج عنها الحلول `x = 2` و `x = 3`."
    },
    {
      "_id": "page_science_1",
      "book_id": "book_science_201",
      "page_number": 1,
      "title": "1.1 Kinetics",
      "title_ar": "1.1 علم الحركة",
      "titleEn": "1.1 Kinetics",
      "titleAr": "1.1 علم الحركة",
      "content": "# 1.1 Kinetics\n\nKinetics is the branch of classical mechanics that concerns the effect of forces on motion. The fundamental formula is Newton's Second Law:\n\n`F = ma`\n\nWhere `F` is force, `m` is mass, and `a` is acceleration.",
      "contentEn": "# 1.1 Kinetics\n\nKinetics is the branch of classical mechanics that concerns the effect of forces on motion. The fundamental formula is Newton's Second Law:\n\n`F = ma`\n\nWhere `F` is force, `m` is mass, and `a` is acceleration.",
      "contentAr": "# 1.1 علم الحركة\n\nعلم الحركة هو فرع من الميكانيكا الكلاسيكية يهتم بتأثير القوى على الحركة. الصيغة الأساسية هي قانون نيوتن الثاني:\n\n`F = ma`\n\nحيث `F` هي القوة، و `m` هي الكتلة، و `a` هو التسارع."
    }
